- *Akaflieg München*, a university-affiliated flying club, designs advanced gliders like the *Mü-32*.
- They use *sensors and data acquisition systems* from *Kistler Group* to perform destructive wing tests.
- A recent test failed prematurely, prompting analysis and redesign to meet *aviation safety standards*.

